  <mads:note type="nonpublic">Cannot identify with Sergius of Resaina, d. 536. New Cath. encyc., c1967, says that Sergius 
    of Resaina was probably the same as Sergius the Grammarian, but Encyc. brit., c1983, gives two separate articles for Sergius 
    and Sergius of Resaina</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">Torrance, I.R. Christology after Chalcedon, 1988: t.p. (Sergius the Monophysite) p. 1, etc. (Sergius the
    Grammarian most common appellation; wrote Greek letters to Severus of Antioch, 515-517; nothing else known of his life or writings; 
    not equated with Sergius of Resaina)</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">Encyc. brit., 15th ed., c1983: Micropaedia, v. 9, p. 68 (Sergius; Roman physician and priest, 5th-6th cent.)</mads:note>
